Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
My hometown has a winter that is practically non existent. Being in Southern India, temparatures remain in the 20's (celcius) which we regard as cold while the same will not be described the same in other parts of the world. Beginning of winter means relief from the incessant monsoon rains, and being not very hot or wet, it is the best time of the year.